some facts, presented in the study:

Crime is not at the heart of gun violence. Of
murders of known circumstance committed in
1992, anonymous killings accounted for only 14
percent of all homicides. Almost half the victims
were either related to or acquainted with their
killer. According to the “Cease Fire” report, the
vast majority of firearms homicides stem from
arguments “turned deadly because of ready
access to a gun.” The crime myth is firmly
debunked by the fact that, of firearms deaths
reported in 1988 (30,565), only 7 percent
(2,179) stemmed from felonious activity.

The FBI’s Uniform Crime Reports addresses the
issue of self-defense. Using FBI standards, justi-
fiable homicide by handgun involving private
citizens happened only 262 times in 1992. At
the national level, this means that the ratio of
lives lost due to gunshots vs. justifiable homicide
was 95 to one.

